summary: Namkook’s first meeting must have been so funny because Jungkook was Namjoon’s biggest fanboy and he probably wanted to say lots...
body:
Namkook’s first meeting must have been so funny because Jungkook was Namjoon’s biggest fanboy and he probably wanted to say lots of things to him about how much he inspired him to pursue his music dreams and stuff and when finding out that they’d be in the same group he probably thought of many things to say

but there he is, finally face to face with Namjoon and… he’s not wearing pants. And all common sense is out and the only sound to leave Jungkook’s mouth is “wow… thighs”

like imagine meeting your idol for the first time and just saying something so fucking thirsty agshsdjdk no wonder he was so shy afterwards

you’d think this kinda stuff is from fanfiction but no this is legit how they first met according to themselves and Hoseok

stan Namkook stan never-ending awkwardness

summary: Эксперты проанализировали сложности Big Hit Entertainment и обсудили возможность ухода BTS
title: Эксперты проанализировали сложности Big Hit Entertainment и обсудили возможность ухода BTS
excerpt: Эксперты проанализировали будущее BTS. Хотя заголовок был сенсационным («Распадутся ли BTS?«), в сегменте появился журналист, который буквально все перерыл в поисках информации и прямо сказал, что вероятность того, что это произойдет, очень низкая. И дело совсем не в BTS, а скорее в Бан Ши Хёке и его теневом прошлом, связанным с долгами, о чем он не решается много […] Сообщение Эксперты проанализировали сложности Big Hit Entertainment и обсудили возможность ухода BTS появились сначала на SHOWASIA - ❶ Новости шоу-бизнеса ❖ K-POP, J-POP, C-POP.

title: I'm sorry (I hate you), I love you (I hate you)
body:
read it on the AO3 at https://ift.tt/2QRA7kI

by thunderingskies

Jungkook has always gone up to the rooftop to escape; to clear his mind of all the things that he wishes he could forget- his loveless relationship, the countless fights, and all the times he wasn’t strong enough to say no.
To feel a piece of freedom, regardless of how fleeting it may be.
But when he goes up one night to find a boy already there and meets Yoongi, he just might have found what he needs more than an escape- a friend.

body:
ARMY Independence Day (rant)

So… I come back to this app and someone is offended about this hashtag trended on Twitter a while ago? Pffft

Istg most people just talk bad about ARMYs for wanting to be out of the Kpop community when it’s the same community that kept on saying we don’t belong in it for years and then hypocritically calls us back when it suits them and they need BTS & ARMYs for clout and views.

Have you seen how Kpoppies memefied BTS Idol’s video to promote their favs? How people blame us for 2k dislikes on their fav’s videos or their fav’s deleted views? Seriously, stop calling yourselves ARMYs if you kept being blinded about all the hate those opportunistic antis throw at us. If you’re a multi, stop throwing BTS under the bus just to please your bloody numerous fandoms.

Also, it’s funny that people get offended when we ARMYs emancipate from the Kpop community. I’ve listened to Korean songs since Rain and BoA were popular and the “umbrella” term “Kpop” wasn’t even thrown around. Not all artists in South Korea could even be categorized as Kpop, do you know? Also, BTS cannot really be categorized as simply “Kpop” since debut. They’ve always been marketed as a K-hip hop/rap group, even in Japan.

BTS themselves appeared to have not straight up & totally identified themselves as Kpop. It’s there in their introductions in their interviews. Why do you think they identify as “South Korean group”? It’s not about superiority but it’s about whatever the hell they want to name themselves as.

Lastly, it’s funny that people are offended that ARMYs turned something that was meant to harm or offend us into a joke. You want us to feel hurt so much? We experience hateful messages everyday. A lot of fandoms have blamed us for many laughably trivial things. You know how many hate hashtags trended against BTS? How many times we had to clean up our timeline? You say that we have toxic people, but other fandoms have that too. Is that your excuse to blaming us ARMYs, those toxic and not? What sacrificial goats we’ve become🙃
